.TH TTFFS 4
.SH NAME
ttffs \- serve ttf fonts as Inferno (sub)fonts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ttffs
[
.B -d
] [
.BI -r " xdpi ydpi"
]
.I fontpath
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Ttffs
serves
.I TrueType
font files as Inferno font/subfont files in arbitrary sizes, over 9P2000.
When a file of the form 
.IR fontname . size .font
is walked, the file
.IR fontname .ttf
in
.I fontpath
is opened, parsed and cached for subsequent.
.I Size
must be a number greater than 1.
The
.IR .font -file
references subfonts of the form
.IR fontname . size . index ,
where
.I index
is a number indicating a glyph range.
.PP
The
.I size
of the font and the dots per inch
.RI ( dpi )
determine the pixel sizes for the generated (sub)fonts.  This makes font sizes independent of the display used.  The
horizontal
.I xdpi
and vertical
.I ydpi
can be set by option
.BR -r ,
and defaults to ``96 96''.
.PP
Option
.B -d
enables debug printing.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# ensure /fonts/ttf/VeraMono.ttf exists
mount -a {ttffs /fonts/ttf} /fonts/ttf
wm/sh -f /fonts/ttf/VeraMono.10.font
.EE
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/cmd/ttffs.b
.SH FILES
.B /fonts/*
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR draw-font (2),
.IR fonts (6).
.SH BUGS
No kerning or subpixel rendering is supported.  Only 8-bit greyscale anti-aliased fonts are served.
